Program: Outlook
Title: My 50 Year Search for my Little Sister
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3cstyvr
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 26 Sep 2017
Two Outlook listeners share their incredible story of a 50 year quest to reunite a family of sisters. Tim FitzHigham is a British comedian who has made not one but two attempts at crossing the Channel between Britain and France in a bath tub. England international rugby stars Mako and Billy Vunipola on life in Tonga, Wales and following in their father's footsteps. At a nature reserve in Chile you will find an unusual creature among the deserts and mountains. Outlook's Jane Chambers went to meet some Chilean penguins and the man who protects them. (Picture credit: Lionel Wolberger.) Show less